About this Privacy Policy
Last modified on: October 14, 2024
This Privacy Policy outlines how and when we collect, manage, store, and protect personal data collected in connection with our app and related services (collectively, the "Services"). It also explains your rights and choices regarding your personal data. For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, Theotin
o (or "we," "our company," or "data controller") refers to Theotino and its subsidiaries, affiliates, representatives, officers, and directors for services that link to this Privacy Policy or otherwise make it available to you.
By using the Services, you consent to the collection and use of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy. This policy is subject to updates, which will be posted here and take effect immediately. We encourage you to review it regularly to stay informed of any changes.
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time by posting a new version on our website or within the app. Any material changes will be communicated through the Services.
Please review this Privacy Policy carefully. By continuing to use our Services, you acknowledge and agree to the practices outlined within.
If there is any difference between the English version and any other language version of this Privacy Policy, the English version will apply (to the extent of the difference and to the extent permitted by applicable law).
Information We May Collect
Our primary objective in collecting user information is to verify user accounts, render good service, fulfill your requirements, and resolve your issues. Rest assured that any information provided by you is well protected according to this Privacy Policy and applicable laws.
When you register for the game and use the Service, we may collect and record the information you provide to us, whether through the game or through social networks or other third-party services ("Account Information").
Personal Information
•
Name:
Your first and last name as provided during account creation.
•
Location:
Your general location based on your IP address.
•
Third-Party IDs:
Any third-party identifiers you provide when linking external accounts (e.g., Facebook, Google).
Usage Information
•
In-Game Purchases:
Records of any purchases made withinthe app.
•
Game Features:
Information about which game features you use most frequently inthe game.
•
Game Preferences:
Your preferred game settings and customization options inthe game.
•
Game Types:
The types of Bingo games you play inthe game.
•
Usage Duration:
How long you spend playingthe game.
•
Usage Patterns:
Information about how you interact withthe game. (e.g., gameplay frequency, time of day).
Technical Information
•
IP Address:
Your internet protocol address.
•
Advertising Identifiers:
Unique identifiers used for targeted advertising inthe game.
•
Cookies:
Small text files stored on your device to track your preferences and usage.
•
Software Development Kits (SDKs):
Third-party tools used for analytics and other purposes inour app.
Device Information
•
Device ID:
A unique identifier for your device.
•
Device Platform:
The operating system (e.g., iOS, Android) your device uses.
•
Firmware:
The version of your device's software.
•
Mobile Carrier:
Your mobile network provider.
•
Preferred Languages:
The languages you select.
Please note, while we do not access your financial information (such as credit card details), any purchases made through third-party platforms (e.g., Apple App Store, Google Play Store) are subject to their respective privacy policies.
In all cases, your data will not be disclosed, rented, loaned, leased, sold, or shared with unaffiliated third parties unless required to provide services or comply with legal obligations.
Permissions and Files
•
Read/Write Permissions:
We may request access to read and write files within the app's directory on your device, such as player log files, to ensure proper functionality and performance of the app.
Communications Data
•
Customer Support Interactions:
Records of your communications with our support team, including any issues reported and resolutions provided.
•
Feedback:
Information from feedback forms and surveys to improve our services.
•
Text Messages:
Data related to text messages for service interactions.
•
Contacts:
Information from your contacts may be collected to enable specific features or services within the app.
Transaction Data
•
Payment Information:
This includes details related to transactions, such as payment methods and billing information.
Other Personal Data
While our game itself does not require access to certain types of personal data, some third-party services (SDKs) integrated into the game may need to collect and use this information to function properly. These data collection processes are necessary for the features provided by these third-party services, not for the core game itself. We want to make sure you are informed about what data might be involved:
•
Music Files:
Audio files like music tracks or playlists that you may upload or access via certain features in the game.
•
Other Audio Files:
Non-music audio recordings, such as sound effects or voice memos, that are generated or interacted with using third-party services.
•
Photos:
Images or photos that you upload or capture within the game, including profile pictures or media shared through third-party services.
•
Videos:
Video files that you upload, record, or interact with via third-party services, including any videos you create or receive.
•
Voice or Sound Recordings:
Audio recordings made through third-party features, such as voice messages or notes.
•
Files and Docs:
Documents of various types (e.g., text files, PDFs) that you upload, store, or access through third-party services integrated into the game.
We are committed to ensuring that data collected by these third-party SDKs is securely managed and handled in compliance with this Privacy Policy and applicable laws.
Please note that while you can purchase virtual goods through the Service, these purchases are processed through third-party platforms (e.g., Apple App Store, Google Play Store). We do not have access to your financial or billing information, such as credit card details. All financial data related to your transactions is securely managed by the third-party platforms according to their own privacy policies.
In all cases of data access and collection, the information you provide will not be disclosed, rented, loaned, leased, sold, or otherwise shared voluntarily with unaffiliated third parties. We may use your information in the following ways:
•
To create and manage your account, ensuring a secure and seamless gameplay experience.
•
To facilitate communication between users.
•
To provide technical support and respond to your queries.
•
To complete transactions that you initiate.
•
To collect feedback for improving our game and to tailor your experience.
With your consent, we may also send you push notifications to keep you informed about game updates, promotions, or other relevant information. You can opt out of receiving these notifications at any time through your device settings.
How We Collect Your Information
We collect your information through various interactions with our services, including:
•
Registering for an account and using the service.
•
Entering a game, competition, promotion, or survey.
•
Providing feedback, requesting support, or otherwise communicating with us.
•
Making a purchase of any virtual product.
•
Connecting with or accessing our services using a third-party ID or log-in, such as a social networking site ID.
How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used for the following purposes:
•
To Provide and Improve Our Services:
We use your information to deliver personalized content, process payments, and enhance the functionality and user experience.
•
To Communicate with You:
We may send you notifications, updates, and promotional emails to keep you informed about new features, offers, and other relevant information.
•
To Perform Advertising and Marketing:
Your information may be used to display personalized ads and promotional content based on your interests and preferences.
•
To Protect Our Rights and Comply with Legal Obligations:
We may use your information to enforce our Terms of Service, prevent fraud or illegal activities, and comply with applicable laws and regulations.
•
For Any Other Business Purpose:
As stated when collecting your personal data or as required by applicable data privacy laws, such as the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).
How We Share Your Information
We may share your personal information with service providers who help us deliver products and services, process purchases, and communicate with you. Additionally, we partner with companies that manage our websites and third-party analytics firms that conduct market research to gain a better understanding of our users. These service providers are permitted to use or disclose your information only to fulfill their contracted responsibilities or as required by law.
•
Third-Party Ad Servers:
We collaborate with third-party ad servers to display advertisements, generate reports, manage ad responses, and analyze site usage. This enables us to deliver relevant marketing messages and ads to users. These ad servers may utilize cookies and tracking technologies to gather information about your visits to our app and other websites, allowing them to serve targeted, interest-based ads. This process involves the anonymous analysis of user behavior to ensure that the ads presented align with your interests.
•
Endpoints:
Your data may be securely transmitted through various communication endpoints to enhance your gaming experience and ensure data integrity and privacy. These endpoints support essential services such as personalized advertising, analytics, user authentication, crash reporting, and customer support. They also include services like Google Firebase for login management and Google Fonts for consistent content display. The partners and services involved include Facebook, Google, Google Firebase & Firebase Crashlytics, Google AdMob, Applovin, Unity, Zendesk, Mintegral, and Appsflyer. These endpoints safeguard your information as it interacts with our partners' systems, ensuring secure data transmission throughout.
•
Data Types:
The types of data we may share include user profiles, in-app activity and usage statistics, purchase and transaction details, and device identifiers (such as device ID or IP address). We ensure that only the necessary information is shared with service providers to perform specific functions related to the services they provide.
•
SDKs (Software Development Kits):
Our platform integrates SDKs from third-party vendors, which may collect and transmit personal data for purposes such as
analytic
, advertising, or payment processing. These SDKs enable the proper functionality of third-party services within our platform. We ensure that these vendors handle your data in compliance with applicable regulations.
