You have the right to be informed when your data is shared or sold. To exercise your right to opt out, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz or through any available in-game support system. Once your request is received, we will ensure your data is no longer shared or sold in any ways you have opted out of.
Third-Party Services
We may work with third-party service providers, such as payment processors, analytics firms, and other specialized services, to help enhance the functionality and performance of our app. These providers operate independently and have their own privacy policies, which govern how they collect, use, and share your information. We recommend that you review these third-party privacy policies to understand how your data may be managed. Although we carefully select these providers and ensure they comply with relevant data protection laws, we do not have control over their privacy practices.
Data Security
We employ stringent security measures to safeguard your personal information from unauthorized access, modification, disclosure, or destruction. This includes the use of industry-standard encryption protocols and secure servers to protect the confidentiality and integrity of your data. Access to your personal information is restricted to employees, agents, contractors, and partners who require it to manage, develop, or enhance our services. These individuals are obligated to maintain strict confidentiality and may face disciplinary actions, including termination, if they fail to comply with these requirements.
Data Protection Officer (DPO):
Theotino
’
s
IT team is responsible for overseeing data protection. If you have any questions or concerns about how your personal information is handled, you can reach out to our Data Protection Officer (DPO) at:
support@luckybingo.xyz
.
Data Retention
We will retain your personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. After that, your information will be securely deleted or anonymized. If you wish to request the deletion of your personal data, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz.
Data Deletion
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal data. To exercise this right, please contact us at
support@luckybingo.xyz
. Upon receiving a valid request, we will:
•
Verify Your Identity:
For your data's security, we may need to confirm your identity before proceeding with your request. This may require you to provide additional information to verify that you are the rightful data subject.
•
Process Your Request:
Once your identity is confirmed, we will review your request and proceed with the deletion of your personal data, unless legal or contractual obligations require us to retain it.
•
Confirm Deletion:
After completing the deletion, we will send you a confirmation that your personal data has been successfully removed from our records.
•
Exceptions:
Please note that certain circumstances may require us to retain your data, such as fulfilling legal obligations, resolving disputes, enforcing agreements, or for other legitimate business purposes.
Your Rights
You have the right to request information about how we process your personal data, access a copy of the personal data we hold about you, and request that your data be modified, corrected, or deleted from our system. You may also request to limit or object to the processing of your personal data.
We will not make any decisions based solely on automated processing (including profiling).
If you have consented to the use of your data, for instance, to receive marketing emails or view personalized advertisements, you can withdraw your consent at any time. Please note that withdrawing consent does not affect the legality of data processing that occurred before your withdrawal.
To exercise any of the above rights, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz.
Cookies
Cookies are small files containing data, often used to identify users anonymously. These files are sent to your browser from the websites you visit and are stored in your device’s memory.
While this service does not directly use cookies, the app may incorporate third-party code and libraries that utilize cookies to gather information and enhance their services. You can choose to accept or decline these cookies, and be notified when a cookie is being sent to your device. However, if you decide to reject cookies, certain features of the service may become unavailable to you.
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
If you are a resident of California, the CCPA grants you the following rights regarding your personal information:
•
Right to Non-Discrimination:
You have the right to not be discriminated against for exercising any of your CCPA rights.
•
Right to Opt-Out:
You have a right to opt out from future sales or sharing of personal information as those terms are defined by the CCPA.
•
Right to Delete:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information that we have collected, subject to certain exceptions.
•
Right to Know:
You have the right to request details about the personal information we collect, use, disclose, and sell, if applicable.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz. We will respond to your request in accordance with the GDPR requirements.
Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA) Rights
If you are a resident of Virginia, the VCDPA provides you with the following rights:
•
Right to Access:
You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you.
•
Right to Correct:
You have the right to request the correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal information.
•
Right to Delete:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected or if you withdraw your consent.
•
Right to Data Portability:
You have the right to request a copy of your personal information in a portable and readily usable format.
•
Right to Opt-Out:
You have the right to opt out of the sale of your personal information or the processing of your data for targeted advertising purposes.
•
Right to Appeal:
If we deny your request to exercise any of these rights, you have the right to appeal our decision.
To exercise any of these rights or to appeal a decision, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz. We will respond to your request or appeal in accordance with the VCDPA requirements.
GDPR Rights for EU Residents
If you are a resident of the European Union (EU), you have certain rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):
•
Right to Access:
You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you and to obtain a copy of that information.
•
Right to Rectification:
You have the right to request that we correct or update any inaccurate or incomplete personal information.
•
Right to Erasure:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, or if you withdraw your consent on which the processing is based.
•
Right to Restrict Processing:
You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information under certain circumstances, such as when you contest the accuracy of the information or when you object to the processing.
•
Right to Data Portability:
You have the right to receive your personal information in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format and to transmit that information to another data controller.
•
Right to Object:
You have the right to object to the processing of your personal information on grounds related to your particular situation, including processing for direct marketing purposes.
•
Rights Related to Automated Decision-Making:
You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produce legal effects concerning you or similarly significantly affect you.
•
Right to Complain:
You have the right to complain to a supervisory authority about our collection and use of your personal data.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz. We will respond to your request in accordance with the GDPR requirements.
Rights of Residents in Brazil under LGPD
If you are a resident of Brazil, the General Data Protection Law (LGPD) grants you the following rights:
•
Right to Access:
You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you and to obtain a copy of that information.
•
Right to Rectification:
You have the right to request the correction or update of inaccurate or incomplete personal information.
•
Right to Erasure:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected or if you withdraw your consent on which the processing is based.
•
Right to Restrict Processing:
You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information under certain circumstances.
•
Right to Data Portability:
You have the right to receive your personal information in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format and to transmit that information to another data controller.
•
Right to Object:
You have the right to object to the processing of your personal information on grounds related to your particular situation, including processing for direct marketing purposes.
•
Right to Review Automated Decisions:
You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produce legal effects concerning you or similarly significantly affect you.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz. We will respond to your request in accordance with the LGPD requirements.
Children's Privacy (COPPA Compliance)
Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 12, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 12. If you believe we have inadvertently gathered such information, please contact us immediately at
support@luckybingo.xyz
, and we will take appropriate steps to delete the data.
Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data
We process your personal data in accordance with applicable data protection laws. The legal grounds for our processing activities include:
1.
Consent
We may process your personal data when you have explicitly given consent for a specific purpose, such as signing up for newsletters, participating in promotions, or receiving marketing communications from us. You have the right to withdraw your consent at any time by contacting us at
support@luckybingo.xyz
. However, withdrawing consent may affect your ability to use certain features or services.
2.
Contractual Necessity
Processing your personal data is often essential for fulfilling the terms of a contract to which you are a party. For example, we may process your data to manage your account, process purchases, provide customer support, and deliver services. Without this processing, we cannot meet our contractual obligations to you.
3.
Legal Obligation
We may be required to process your personal data to comply with legal obligations imposed by laws, regulations, or government authorities. This includes obligations related to tax compliance, financial reporting, record-keeping, and responding to lawful requests from public authorities. Any data processed under this basis will comply with relevant legal standards.
4.
Legitimate Interests
We may process your personal data based on our legitimate interests, as long as this does not override your fundamental rights and freedoms. Our legitimate interests include:
￮
Fraud Prevention and Security:
We process data to monitor, prevent, and detect fraudulent activities, unauthorized access, and misuse of our services, ensuring your account and our platform are protected.
￮
Service Improvement:
We analyze user behavior and feedback to enhance our services
’
functionality, performance, and user experience. This includes research and analysis to better understand user preferences and trends.
￮
Marketing and Advertising:
We may use your data to personalize and deliver targeted marketing communications, promotions, and ads relevant to your interests, providing a more tailored experience.
￮
Business Operations:
We process data to support daily business operations, such as managing customer relationships, optimizing services, and conducting market research.
5.
Public Task
In some cases, we may process your personal data to perform tasks carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in us. This may apply to situations where data processing is required for regulatory compliance, public health, safety, or other matters of public interest.
Changes To This Policy
We are dedicated to keeping our Privacy Policy up-to-date and reflective of our current data practices. Therefore, we reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will become effective immediately upon being posted within our app or on our website.
1.
Notification of Changes
If we make any major changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you through prominent methods, such as in-app notifications, emails, or update notices on our website. We encourage you to review these notices to stay informed about how your data is being used.
2.
Continued Use of Services
By continuing to use our services after any updates to this Privacy Policy, you are acknowledging and agreeing to the revised policy. If you do not agree with the updated policy, you should discontinue using our services and contact us to discuss your concerns.
3.
Periodic Review
We recommend that you periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed about our data protection practices. This will help you better understand how we collect, use, and share your personal information, as well as your rights regarding that data.
How to Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please do not hesitate to contact us at support@luckybingo.xyz.